WEBVTT

1
00:00:35.650 --> 00:00:36.981
Game over.

2
00:00:37.085 --> 00:00:39.553
I'll fuckin' kill you!

3
00:00:39.654 --> 00:00:41.884
You fuckin' bitch!

4
00:00:42.924 --> 00:00:44.391
You bitch!

5
00:00:46.160 --> 00:00:48.219
I'll fuckin' kill you!

6
00:02:17.018 --> 00:02:19.145
Daniel!

7
00:05:15.363 --> 00:05:18.799
Secure the flank!
Left side clear?

8
00:05:18.899 --> 00:05:20.332
We're clear!

9
00:05:20.434 --> 00:05:22.868
Left side's clear.
Let's move!

10
00:05:35.950 --> 00:05:37.417
Oh, my God.

11
00:05:39.954 --> 00:05:41.478
Someone call Kerry.

12
00:05:41.589 --> 00:05:45.389
The call came in at 11:45.
The woman heard an explosion.

13
00:05:45.493 --> 00:05:46.824
The fire department was
the first on the scene.

14
00:05:46.927 --> 00:05:48.019
Kerry.

15
00:05:48.129 --> 00:05:50.359
- Is it him?
- Before you go in there--

16
00:05:50.464 --> 00:05:52.591
Eric. Is it him?

17
00:05:52.700 --> 00:05:53.894
We don't know yet.

18
00:06:02.410 --> 00:06:04.105
It's not Detective Matthews.

19
00:06:17.858 --> 00:06:18.825
What happened?

20
00:06:18.926 --> 00:06:22.327
The victim was held
in place by these chains.

21
00:07:01.802 --> 00:07:04.862
Hello, Troy.

22
00:07:04.972 --> 00:07:07.497
I wanna play a game.

23
00:07:07.608 --> 00:07:09.872
This game will take place
in a room not much bigger

24
00:07:09.977 --> 00:07:12.707
than the room you've
spent most of your life in.

25
00:07:12.813 --> 00:07:14.440
A prison cell.

26
00:07:14.548 --> 00:07:16.982
Despite all of the advantages
and privileges

27
00:07:17.084 --> 00:07:18.711
that you were given at birth,

28
00:07:18.819 --> 00:07:23.017
you have returned
to prison again and again.

29
00:07:23.124 --> 00:07:26.423
More comfortable in chains
than you are in freedom.

30
00:07:26.527 --> 00:07:30.054
Tonight we will see how
far you are willing to go

31
00:07:30.164 --> 00:07:32.689
to break those chains
once and for all.

32
00:07:32.800 --> 00:07:34.290
Live or die, Troy.

33
00:07:34.401 --> 00:07:36.528
Make your choice.

34
00:07:55.523 --> 00:07:57.923
This was the bomb.

35
00:07:58.025 --> 00:08:03.588
All he had to do was release himself
from each of the chains...

36
00:08:03.697 --> 00:08:07.656
walk out the door before it went off.

37
00:08:09.703 --> 00:08:11.330
All he had to do?

38
00:08:55.883 --> 00:08:57.714
Oh, God.

39
00:09:33.854 --> 00:09:36.220
Fuck! Fuck!

40
00:09:53.474 --> 00:09:55.874
I really had this feeling
it was going to be him.

41
00:09:55.976 --> 00:10:01.380
Kerry, Eric is a missing persons case,
not a homicide case.

42
00:10:03.150 --> 00:10:07.109
I've been having nightmares
where I see him.

43
00:10:11.992 --> 00:10:14.893
I'm never going to be able
to forgive myself for what happened.

44
00:10:14.995 --> 00:10:17.395
Listen.
It's not your fault.

45
00:10:17.498 --> 00:10:18.795
It's always somebody's fault.

46
00:10:18.899 --> 00:10:20.366
That somebody isn't you.

47
00:10:20.467 --> 00:10:22.731
That someone is still out there.

48
00:10:22.836 --> 00:10:26.738
Put all your anger into finding them
and putting them away.

49
00:10:26.840 --> 00:10:28.137
All right?

50
00:10:29.009 --> 00:10:31.910
What I don't understand is

51
00:10:32.012 --> 00:10:33.570
how the hell could Jigsaw
do all of this?

52
00:10:33.681 --> 00:10:36.309
He was damn near on his deathbed
the last time we saw him.

53
00:10:39.186 --> 00:10:40.448
I'm not so sure he did.

54
00:10:40.554 --> 00:10:42.818
So far this doesn't follow
any of his patterns.

55
00:10:42.923 --> 00:10:44.254
Meaning?

56
00:10:44.358 --> 00:10:47.020
Well... how'd you get in here?

57
00:10:47.127 --> 00:10:49.391
- We cut the door down.
- Why?

58
00:10:49.496 --> 00:10:52.556
Because somebody heard
an explosion and called us.

59
00:10:52.666 --> 00:10:54.964
I mean, why did you
have to cut the door down?

60
00:10:55.069 --> 00:10:56.798
It was welded shut.

61
00:10:56.904 --> 00:10:58.269
Bloody truck couldn't get in here.

62
00:10:58.372 --> 00:10:59.634
Exactly.

63
00:10:59.740 --> 00:11:01.708
I don't follow.

64
00:11:01.809 --> 00:11:04.175
If the aim of Jigsaw's game was
to get out before the bomb went off,

65
00:11:04.278 --> 00:11:06.041
then why was the door
welded shut?

66
00:11:06.146 --> 00:11:08.444
The guy couldn't get out if he wanted to.

67
00:11:08.549 --> 00:11:11.746
You won't believe this.
We got the tape out clean.

68
00:12:04.104 --> 00:12:07.301
Hello, Troy.
I wanna play a game.

69
00:12:09.576 --> 00:12:13.068
Live or die, Troy.
Make your choice.

70
00:14:12.232 --> 00:14:13.256
Hello, Kerry.

71
00:14:14.735 --> 00:14:16.225
I want to play a game.

72
00:14:16.336 --> 00:14:20.602
Up until now you have spent
your life among the dead

73
00:14:20.707 --> 00:14:22.299
piecing together
their final moments.

74
00:14:22.409 --> 00:14:25.708
You are good at this because you,
like them,

75
00:14:25.812 --> 00:14:27.109
are also dead.

76
00:14:27.214 --> 00:14:29.876
Dead on the inside.

77
00:14:29.983 --> 00:14:34.147
You identify more
with a cold corpse

78
00:14:34.254 --> 00:14:36.154
than you do
with a living human.

79
00:14:36.256 --> 00:14:39.384
I believe you want
to join your true family,

80
00:14:39.493 --> 00:14:42.587
indeed, your only family,
in death.

81
00:14:44.031 --> 00:14:45.658
The device you are wearing

82
00:14:45.766 --> 00:14:48.360
is hooked into your ribcage.

83
00:14:48.468 --> 00:14:50.527
And by the time
this tape is finished,

84
00:14:50.637 --> 00:14:53.834
you will have one minute
to find a way out.

85
00:14:53.941 --> 00:14:57.308
At the end of that minute,
you should know

86
00:14:57.411 --> 00:15:00.505
better than anyone
what happens then.

87
00:15:00.614 --> 00:15:03.708
There is a simple key
that will unlock the harness, Kerry.

88
00:15:03.817 --> 00:15:05.375
It is right in front of you.

89
00:15:05.485 --> 00:15:09.251
All you have to do is
reach in and take it.

90
00:15:10.457 --> 00:15:11.947
But do it quickly.

91
00:15:12.059 --> 00:15:17.087
The acid will dissolve the key
in a matter of seconds.

92
00:15:17.197 --> 00:15:19.563
Make your choice.

93
00:16:53.560 --> 00:16:54.686
You.

94
00:17:34.101 --> 00:17:36.262
I gotta be at the hospital by 9.

95
00:17:38.905 --> 00:17:41.373
It's Tuesday.
I thought you started at 11.

96
00:17:41.475 --> 00:17:45.309
Yeah, well, they change
things on me last minute.

97
00:17:45.412 --> 00:17:46.902
Well, you better head off, then.

98
00:17:54.654 --> 00:17:55.814
You're not gonna take a shower?

99
00:17:57.290 --> 00:18:01.624
Nah. I'm just gonna take
a shower at the hospital.

100
00:18:01.728 --> 00:18:06.461
Can we just...
talk for five minutes?

101
00:18:06.566 --> 00:18:10.434
How about we just make eye contact
for five seconds?

102
00:18:10.537 --> 00:18:11.629
What's wrong?

103
00:18:11.738 --> 00:18:16.903
Nothing.
Just... everything.

104
00:18:19.579 --> 00:18:21.137
Lynn.

105
00:18:21.248 --> 00:18:22.977
What is it you want from me, Chris?

106
00:18:24.951 --> 00:18:25.940
A divorce.

107
00:18:35.295 --> 00:18:36.284
MPA.

108
00:18:37.731 --> 00:18:39.426
Car skidded into oncoming traffic.

109
00:18:41.001 --> 00:18:41.899
Pressure?

110
00:18:42.002 --> 00:18:43.196
80 over, palp.
Pulse is thready.

111
00:18:43.303 --> 00:18:45.134
Ready? 1, 2, 3.

112
00:18:45.238 --> 00:18:47.968
- Where's Lynn?
- Page Dr. Denlon.

113
00:18:48.074 --> 00:18:48.972
Set up an art-line.

114
00:18:49.075 --> 00:18:50.042
Dr. Lynn Denlon,

115
00:18:50.143 --> 00:18:51.474
please report
to trauma immediately.

116
00:18:52.012 --> 00:18:54.446
Dr. Lynn Denlon, please
report to trauma immediately.

117
00:18:56.349 --> 00:18:57.316
Lynn!

118
00:18:59.286 --> 00:19:01.083
Check this out.
Hermaphony.

119
00:19:01.188 --> 00:19:04.248
Pressure down to 70.
He's going into shock.

120
00:19:04.357 --> 00:19:06.348
Get an OR ready.
We gotta crack his chest.

121
00:19:06.460 --> 00:19:08.052
Do we get a bolus?
500 wide open?

122
00:19:08.161 --> 00:19:09.128
No.

123
00:19:10.797 --> 00:19:12.389
What?

124
00:19:16.069 --> 00:19:17.696
- No air entry on the right side.
- And?

125
00:19:17.804 --> 00:19:19.669
Let's get a chest tube in him.

126
00:19:19.773 --> 00:19:22.708
We gotta get him to OR now.

127
00:19:22.809 --> 00:19:24.709
His stats are dropping.
He's gonna code.

128
00:19:27.280 --> 00:19:28.247
I'm doin' it.

129
00:19:38.725 --> 00:19:40.283
I'm getting a rush of air.

130
00:19:40.393 --> 00:19:43.419
Stats are improving.
Pressure back to 80.

131
00:19:43.530 --> 00:19:45.998
Pressure normal.

132
00:20:02.849 --> 00:20:04.680
If you got something on your mind,
go upstairs to psych.

133
00:20:04.784 --> 00:20:06.411
Just don't bring it in here.

134
00:20:06.520 --> 00:20:08.147
We don't have any seconds to spare, Lynn.

135
00:20:08.255 --> 00:20:10.849
The woman standing in front of me
had to be dragged

136
00:20:10.957 --> 00:20:13.790
from the locker room
to put a chest tube in a trauma patient?

137
00:20:13.894 --> 00:20:15.828
Lynn Denlon should have been
the first one there.

138
00:20:19.633 --> 00:20:20.600
Lynn.

139
00:20:21.635 --> 00:20:22.602
Lynn!

140
00:20:56.636 --> 00:20:57.933
What the hell?

141
00:20:58.471 --> 00:20:59.768
I'm locked in!

142
00:20:59.873 --> 00:21:01.864
Is anybody there?

143
00:21:01.975 --> 00:21:03.203
Hello?

144
00:21:11.318 --> 00:21:12.945
Anybody here?

145
00:22:36.970 --> 00:22:40.201
Help! Help me!

146
00:22:42.742 --> 00:22:44.642
Help!

147
00:22:49.849 --> 00:22:52.044
Who are you?
Who are you?

148
00:22:52.152 --> 00:22:53.949
What is this?

149
00:22:56.256 --> 00:22:59.987
What are you doing?

150
00:23:04.798 --> 00:23:06.060
Are you gonna behave?

151
00:23:13.907 --> 00:23:15.272
Let's go.

152
00:23:17.377 --> 00:23:20.005
What is this place?
What is this place?

153
00:23:29.122 --> 00:23:31.818
What is... this place?

154
00:23:38.898 --> 00:23:41.560
Who are you?
Who are you?

155
00:23:46.539 --> 00:23:48.097
Hello, Dr. Denlon.

156
00:23:48.208 --> 00:23:52.941
You may not remember me,
but I most certainly remember you.

157
00:23:53.046 --> 00:23:58.609
I was a guest at your hospital once.

158
00:24:01.821 --> 00:24:02.788
Where am I?

159
00:24:06.059 --> 00:24:07.959
Do you remember me?

160
00:24:17.470 --> 00:24:18.767
I've seen you on television.

161
00:24:20.607 --> 00:24:23.041
Lawrence Gordon was your doctor.

162
00:24:23.143 --> 00:24:26.635
I was his patient,
and he was mine.

163
00:24:28.148 --> 00:24:29.911
As you can see from that report,

164
00:24:30.016 --> 00:24:31.881
my prognosis isn't good.

165
00:24:33.586 --> 00:24:35.645
Would you agree?

166
00:24:42.562 --> 00:24:44.962
There's no preventative treatment
for what you have.

167
00:24:45.064 --> 00:24:48.033
I remember you saying that
to me once before

168
00:24:48.134 --> 00:24:50.694
in almost the exact same tone.

169
00:24:50.804 --> 00:24:54.467
Leave it to a doctor to find such a cold,
clinical way

170
00:24:54.574 --> 00:24:57.668
of saying I'm a dead man walking.

171
00:24:57.777 --> 00:25:00.439
Looking at me,
how long would you say I have left?

172
00:25:00.547 --> 00:25:03.675
I'd have to examine you.

173
00:25:03.783 --> 00:25:06.650
Even then,
a frontal lobe tumor is unpredictable.

174
00:25:06.753 --> 00:25:10.154
The growth depends on the rate of mitosis
versus apoptosis--

175
00:25:10.256 --> 00:25:14.693
I'm sorry, but there's all this crude
medical equipment around me

176
00:25:14.794 --> 00:25:18.252
causing you to believe
that you're still inside a hospital.

177
00:25:18.364 --> 00:25:19.661
No.

178
00:25:19.766 --> 00:25:21.233
Then why are you speaking to me

179
00:25:21.334 --> 00:25:24.394
in that graduate school
medical jargon?

180
00:25:26.973 --> 00:25:27.871
Look at me!

181
00:25:30.443 --> 00:25:32.274
Now, you look at me.

182
00:25:32.378 --> 00:25:34.903
I asked you a simple question.

183
00:25:35.014 --> 00:25:36.743
Based on your experience,

184
00:25:36.850 --> 00:25:40.377
how long do you think I have left?

185
00:25:40.486 --> 00:25:42.613
It's not a simple answer.

186
00:25:42.722 --> 00:25:47.682
Based on your file,
I'd say... not long.

187
00:25:56.302 --> 00:25:58.497
Death is a surprise party.

188
00:25:58.605 --> 00:26:04.339
Unless, of course,
you're already dead on the inside.

189
00:26:07.614 --> 00:26:09.104
Unless you're the type of person

190
00:26:09.215 --> 00:26:13.083
who swallows antidepressants
to hide the pain, huh?

191
00:26:13.186 --> 00:26:15.347
Turns their back on their husband.

192
00:26:15.455 --> 00:26:17.514
Neglects their child.

193
00:26:17.624 --> 00:26:20.184
Who has every possible
advantage in life

194
00:26:20.293 --> 00:26:22.761
but chooses not to advance.

195
00:26:22.862 --> 00:26:24.762
What do you want from me?

196
00:26:26.332 --> 00:26:28.095
What do I want?

197
00:26:30.203 --> 00:26:31.602
I want to play a game.

198
00:26:35.074 --> 00:26:38.566
The rules of the game are simple.

199
00:26:38.678 --> 00:26:42.273
The consequences
for breaking them are great.

200
00:26:42.382 --> 00:26:43.349
Death.

201
00:26:45.952 --> 00:26:48.614
You're being tested.
Your will is being tested.

202
00:26:48.721 --> 00:26:50.655
Your will to keep someone alive.

203
00:26:50.757 --> 00:26:51.917
Can you do that?

204
00:26:52.025 --> 00:26:54.755
Can you follow the rules
and grant someone the gift of life?

205
00:26:54.861 --> 00:26:57.796
What is this?
No! Get it--

206
00:26:57.897 --> 00:27:03.426
No! No! What is this!
What are you doing to me?

207
00:27:09.208 --> 00:27:13.269
The device that you're wearing
is linked to my heart rate monitor.

208
00:27:13.379 --> 00:27:18.180
The second that heart rate monitor flatlines
or you move out of range,

209
00:27:18.284 --> 00:27:21.151
an explosion will go off in that collar.

210
00:27:21.254 --> 00:27:25.657
Your life and my life
will end simultaneously.

211
00:27:26.893 --> 00:27:28.952
Please.
Please don't do this to me.

212
00:27:29.062 --> 00:27:31.895
I have a family.
I have a family.

213
00:27:31.998 --> 00:27:34.364
Let me give you
the simple version.

214
00:27:35.902 --> 00:27:39.531
You will keep him alive,
whatever it takes.

215
00:27:39.639 --> 00:27:44.167
No excuses.
No equivocations.

216
00:27:44.277 --> 00:27:46.074
No crying.

217
00:27:46.179 --> 00:27:48.909
What do you mean,
keep him alive?

218
00:27:51.751 --> 00:27:56.552
Out there, on those screens,
we have another test subject.

219
00:27:56.656 --> 00:27:58.715
A man.

220
00:28:00.493 --> 00:28:04.657
He will face a series of tests.

221
00:28:04.764 --> 00:28:09.963
You have to keep John alive
until he makes it through.

222
00:28:11.004 --> 00:28:15.065
If he completes all of his tests
and John is still breathing,

223
00:28:15.174 --> 00:28:17.734
then I will remove your collar...

224
00:28:19.612 --> 00:28:21.273
and you're free to go.

225
00:28:22.548 --> 00:28:25.039
You're a vital piece
of my puzzle, Dr. Denlon.

226
00:28:25.151 --> 00:28:28.917
A critical part of what could be
my final test.

227
00:28:30.723 --> 00:28:34.523
Amanda,
it's time to start our game.

228
00:29:05.525 --> 00:29:06.856
Help!

229
00:29:13.332 --> 00:29:14.299
Hello!

230
00:29:17.170 --> 00:29:19.138
Is there anybody out there?

231
00:29:28.881 --> 00:29:31.145
Hello, Jeff.

232
00:29:31.250 --> 00:29:32.877
Over the past few years,

233
00:29:32.985 --> 00:29:35.920
you have become a shell
of your former self...

234
00:29:36.022 --> 00:29:39.219
consumed with hatred
and vengeance.

235
00:29:39.325 --> 00:29:43.125
Vengeance against the drunk driver
who killed your only son.

236
00:29:43.229 --> 00:29:48.565
Vengeance against the killer,
who to your surprise and dismay,

237
00:29:48.668 --> 00:29:52.866
was set free after a hasty trial.

238
00:29:52.972 --> 00:29:57.272
Today, however,
it is you who will be put on trial.

239
00:29:57.376 --> 00:30:02.313
To escape from where you are,
you will have to face a series of tests.

240
00:30:02.415 --> 00:30:06.715
You will have to suffer
to move forward through each of them.

241
00:30:06.819 --> 00:30:11.085
But with each one,
you will also have a chance...

242
00:30:11.190 --> 00:30:14.318
a chance to forgive.

243
00:30:14.427 --> 00:30:15.689
When you complete the tests,

244
00:30:15.795 --> 00:30:19.231
I promise you
you will finally come face to face

245
00:30:19.332 --> 00:30:22.233
with the man responsible
for the loss of your child.

246
00:30:22.335 --> 00:30:25.395
That will be your ultimate test.

247
00:30:25.505 --> 00:30:28.065
Can you forgive him?

248
00:30:29.609 --> 00:30:30.701
You better hurry, though.

249
00:30:30.810 --> 00:30:34.041
In two hours, the doors will lock,

250
00:30:34.147 --> 00:30:37.310
and this place
will become your tomb.

251
00:30:37.416 --> 00:30:40.943
This is what you've
been waiting for, Jeff.

252
00:30:41.053 --> 00:30:42.645
Let the game begin.

253
00:30:42.755 --> 00:30:44.655
Help!

254
00:31:11.317 --> 00:31:13.877
You fucking killed my son.

255
00:31:13.986 --> 00:31:16.716
Don't you fuckin' beg.

256
00:31:16.822 --> 00:31:20.952
Do you know who I am?

257
00:31:22.929 --> 00:31:25.056
I'll fuckin' teach you,
you motherfucker.

258
00:31:34.607 --> 00:31:36.734
This is what you fuckin' deserve.

259
00:31:57.797 --> 00:31:59.321
Where is it?

260
00:31:59.432 --> 00:32:01.059
What?

261
00:32:03.135 --> 00:32:04.329
Where is it?

262
00:32:11.844 --> 00:32:13.243
